<h2>The weather in November 2019</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
The European-average temperature for November 2019 was 1.5&#176;C warmer than the average November from 1981-2010, but cooler than several other Novembers in this data record, most notably the Novembers of 2015 and 2009, when European-average temperatures were respectively 2.3&#176;C and 2.2&#176;C above the 1981-2010 average
<br><br>
In general, high pressure areas dominated over central and eastern Europe while low pressure areas could be found over western Europe. As a result mild southern tot southeastern winds prevailed over central/eastern and southeastern Europe, which led not only to very mild nights but also to an extreme anomaly in maximum temperatures. In contrast with these relative warm regions, the northwestern half of Scandinavia was far too cold due to a high pressure area from the Artic. This led to a series of cold nights.
<br><br>
