<h3>Precipitation</h3>
The overview of precipitation for November 2019 shows wetter than average conditions for large parts of central and western Europe. Many regions saw much above average precipitation. This was particularly the case along the central Mediterranean, where it was often linked to short-lived heavy precipitation events, which in many cases led to flooding in multiple localities in Italy, France, Montenegro and Greece, with widespread impacts including loss of life.
<br><br>
Drier than average conditions prevailed over the most eastern parts of Europe and around the Black Sea. Other regions with drier than average conditions include parts of the southern and eastern Iberian Peninsula, Iceland and western and northern Scandinavia. In particular southwestern Norway saw a very dry November, with many stations recording the lowest precipitation amount for any November according to MET Norway's long-term record.
