<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
A strong positive anomaly in cloud cover and corresponding negative anomaly in radiation can be found over large parts of central/southern and southeastern Europe. Many days of southerly winds in the Alpine region produced a lot of "stau-clouds" which led to an extreme decrease in radiation over northern Italy. The northwestern half of Scandinavia had a positive anomaly in radiation due to the high-pressure areas over the extreme northern parts.
